The paper discusses a system that combines database and machine learning ideas to help develop knowledge base construction (KBC) systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses techniques for extraction and cleaning of unstructured information, which could fall under the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper proposes two methods for incremental inference, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
